Diagnosis.
Body black (
Fig. 13
); mandible and legs dark brown; third antennomere (including annellus) 1.5 × longer than fourth antennomere and setae of fifth and sixth antennomere in 2 rows (
Fig. 14F
); eye in dorsal view almost equal to temple (
Fig. 14H
); eye in lateral view 1.4 × higher than wide (
Fig. 12J
); frons smooth posteriorly, but with some reticulate-rugosity between antennal sockets (
Fig. 14H
); vertex and temple smooth and with sparse long setae (
Fig. 14H
); face sculptured and with some rugae medially, 2.5 × wider than high, distinct convex medially, with a short medio-longitudinal ridge and long setae near eye (
Fig. 14I
); clypeus small and semielliptical, with some punctures and long setae (
Fig. 14I
); precoxal sulcus widely crenulate, only reaching anterior edge of epicnemial area, removed from middle coxa (
Fig. 14B
); notauli incomplete, only present anteriorly, distinctly crenulated (
Fig. 14C
); medio-posterior depression deep and long, with some carinae, almost extending to middle of mesoscutum, mesoscutum smooth and glabrous (
Fig. 14C
); surface of propodeum densely reticulaterugose, with medio-longitudinal carina distinctly protruding in lateral view, areola absent posteriorly, spiracle of propodeum large, diameter of opening (including membrane) more than 1/5 of minimum distance from spiracle to anterior edge of propodeum (
Fig. 14D
); pterostigma wide and hemispherically shaped, 3.2 × longer than its maximum width (
Fig. 14A
); hind coxa smooth (
Fig. 14M
); length of first tergite almost equal to its apical width, its surface finely longitudinally striate (
Fig. 14D
); ovipositor sheath very short, setose part of ovipositor sheath 0.04 × as long as fore wing (total visible sheath 0.06 times), and 0.2 × as long as hind tibia (
Fig. 14G
).

Head. Transverse, width of head 2.1 × its lateral length, and 1.5 × wider than mesoscutum (
Fig. 14F
); antenna with 34 antennomere, third antennomere (including annellus) 1.5 × longer than fourth antennomere, length of third, fourth and penultimate antennomere 2.5, 1.4 and 1.3 × their width, respectively (
Fig. 14F
); length of maxillary palp 1.3 × height of head (
Fig. 14J
); eye in dorsal view almost equal to temple (
Fig. 14H
); eye in lateral view 1.4 × higher than wide (
Fig. 14J
); frons smooth posteriorly, but with some reticulate-rugosity between antennal sockets (
Fig. 14H
); vertex and temple smooth and with few long setae (
Fig. 14H
); OOL:diameter of ocellus:POL= 15:5:3; face sculptured and with some rugae medially, 2.5 × wider than high, distinct convex medially and with a short medio-longitudinal ridge and long setae near eye (
Fig. 14I
); clypeus small and semi-elliptical, with some punctures and long setae (
Fig. 14I
); mandible enlarged apically, dorsal tooth enlarged, lobe-shaped (
Fig. 14K
), ventral tooth medium-sized and lobe-shaped (
Fig. 14L
), middle tooth curved and acute, with wide incision between first and second tooth (
Fig. 14K
), medial length of mandible 1.5 × its maximum width.

